					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Here's two more ideas:<br /><br />2 ICs:<br />Inverter + RAM<br />→ Map 8KB RAM into PPU $0xxx and $2xxx for 4KB CHR-RAM slice and 4-screen mirroring, inverter makes <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">NOT A12</tt> to decode 4KB ROM (or 4KB window) in $1xxx<br /><br />3 ICs:<br />Latch, Logic, quad 1-of-2 multiplexer<br />→ e.g. using a 7408: Make PPU $0000-$17FF fixed with a 2KB bank at $1800-$1FFF by <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">SEL←PPUA12 AND PPUA11</tt> and using the multiplexer to either pass 0,0,A12,A11 to the CHR or the latched value.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

